'''Otowatatsumi Shrine''' (おとわたつみじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} located in {{ill|lt=Izuhara Town|Q11410123|WD=Q11410123|1=Izuhara}}, {{ill|lt=Tsushima City|Q991032|WD=Q991032|1=Tsushima, Nagasaki}}, {{ill|lt=Nagasaki Prefecture|Q169376|WD=Q169376|1=Nagasaki Prefecture}}. It is considered a candidate site (ronsha) for the Shikinaisha Watatsumi Shrine recorded in the '{{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}'.

=== Overview ===
The date of establishment is unknown; however, according to shrine tradition, {{ill|lt=Empress Jingū|Q232803|WD=Q232803|1=Empress Jingū}} moored her ship at this location and enshrined the deity.

It is the only “Watatsumi Shrine” in {{ill|lt=Shimoken District|Q10868678|WD=Q10868678|1=Shimoagata district}} (the {{ill|lt=Watatsumi Shrine|Q18457651|WD=Q18457651|1=Watazumi Shrine}} area was formerly in {{ill|lt=Kamikō District|Q10868208|WD=Q10868208|1=Kamiagata district}}), and in the *Tsushima Shrine Gazetteer* it is recorded as “Wadatsumi Daimyōjin.”<ref> Shikinaisha Research Association, *Report of the Shikinaisha Survey* ({{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Kōgakkan University|1=UNKNOWN}} Press)</ref>

In the full text of the *Tsushima Shrine Gazetteer*, the description is no different from that of an ordinary village tutelary shrine; no distinctive characteristics as a Watatsumi Shrine are noted, nor is there any indication of traditions associated with official shrines.<ref> Shikinaisha Research Association, *Report of the Shikinaisha Survey* (Kōgakkan University Press)</ref>

